{"title":"Bradicardia-2024","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Cardiología/Bradicardia-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Bradicardia","guid":"QZMQqqQs7pIuz9JTuNT7tw","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Perlas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"- ¿Cuál es el límite inferior de frecuencia cardíaca para definir bradicardia?","guid":"-GtkZkpOlIMjJ5sJtWdK6g","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"- < 60 lpm en adultos (1)","guid":"h8GxT4HrEbk1CDYVm1jV7w","children":[]}]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"- ¿Cuál es la clasificación fisiopatológica de la bradicardia?","guid":"WDJYVX_I35N3UNRgawRq9Q","children":[{"id":"5","parent":"4","text":"- Alteraciones en la formación del impulso (disfunción sinusal) o en la conducción AV (bloqueos) (2)","guid":"00mnOT3JxWYGVKMPkcx75A","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"6","parent":"0","text":"Definición:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"7","parent":"6","text":"- Frecuencia cardíaca < 60 lpm en adultos (1)","guid":"mOAzJd8q26o8ytp2UD2tSw","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"6","text":"- Reseña histórica: En 1901 Karel F. Wenckebach publica su trabajo sobre\\Nbloqueos AV de segundo grado, siendo base para clasificación actual (3)","guid":"0QBDC3YQkZUKH_gWyTRObQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"9","parent":"0","text":"Fisiopatología:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"10","parent":"9","text":"- Fisiología:","guid":"nhG4seJnpRSVaIkM7oR3Dg","children":[{"id":"11","parent":"10","text":"- Automatismo sinusal (60-100 lpm) determina frecuencia cardíaca normal","guid":"8MKZ4qQ8ntT3FeJocXm1Nw","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"10","text":"- Conducción AV permite transmisión del impulso a ventrículos","guid":"9rDmZ7tydsR2xZDz9pO_Qg","children":[]}]},{"id":"13","parent":"9","text":"- Fisiopatología:","guid":"H-Ud22vsvcdGlD_HE_X6nQ","children":[{"id":"14","parent":"13","text":"- Alteración del automatismo sinusal (enfermedad del nodo, fármacos, etc.) (2)","guid":"ElF3dg2mgGpr21BxD_aUjw","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"13","text":"- Alteración de la conducción AV (bloqueos AV congénitos o adquiridos) (2)","guid":"QBOg7rPQmn1HhuCxLzkDBA","children":[]}]},{"id":"16","parent":"9","text":"- Objetivos terapéuticos:","guid":"c01d2DuHdHoGj4clCyL-Fw","children":[{"id":"17","parent":"16","text":"- Tratar causa subyacente y prevenir síntomas y complicaciones (síncope, insuficiencia cardíaca)","guid":"BBnmAKUE2mRRfC7nakCoaA","children":[]}]},{"id":"18","parent":"9","text":"- Investigación futura: Mejores estrategias para identificar y tratar causas reversibles","guid":"swfuRZwJHyv78oLE6gb3Xw","children":[]}]},{"id":"19","parent":"0","text":"Epidemiología:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"20","parent":"19","text":"- Prevalencia <60 lpm: 0. 6-2.2% en adultos (4)","guid":"kjyeEysN-afna8-dk1N7DQ","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"19","text":"- En Chile, datos limitados. Un estudio en población geriátrica mostró prevalencia del 6.2% (5)","guid":"XH46RXn3Lu0q8M-GAdxwzw","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"19","text":"- Morbilidad: Bradicardia sintomática asociada a reducción de capacidad funcional y calidad de vida","guid":"s3SLqQJXnK6YtfGxzmn2mQ","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"19","text":"- Letalidad baja, pero bradicardia puede precipitar síncope o insuf. cardíaca en susceptibles","guid":"DziTV2Y1sNbFer1Xsbw6tQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"24","parent":"0","text":"Factores de riesgo:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"25","parent":"24","text":"- Edad avanzada (RR 2.1 vs <60 años) (6)","guid":"KNQVI9ffgTwSXITnMSYqUQ","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"24","text":"- Enfermedad estructural cardíaca (RR 3.2) (6)","guid":"-hykTeL2EEQGHbuHijUNHQ","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"24","text":"- Fármacos cronotrópicos negativos\\N(betabloqueadores, antagonistas del calcio, etc.)","guid":"RQ3ezw4DF2aJ5l1Bf0P9dw","children":[]}]},{"id":"28","parent":"0","text":"Causas:","guid":"MRBPY8ZhK7CX6e8nRCBXVw","children":[{"id":"29","parent":"28","text":"- Fisiológica","guid":"gqOyty5LXKM_lbAyTAQTdA","children":[{"id":"30","parent":"29","text":"- Atletas bien entrenados (por aumento del tono vagal)","guid":"ERrLita5TIoqs7xjNH9xpQ","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"29","text":"- Durante el sueño (especialmente en jóvenes)","guid":"2eIlHeTTR-FpgrHxaTguDQ","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"29","text":"- Estimulación del seno carotídeo (tos, afeitarse, tumores del cuello)","guid":"uUeVdmnFVLEO1vxPNedH8g","children":[]}]},{"id":"33","parent":"28","text":"- Disfunción\\Nsinusal intrínseca","guid":"IKQNn9OY08jKiypQTMpdjA","children":[{"id":"34","parent":"33","text":"- Enfermedad degenerativa idiopática (fibrosis del nodo sinusal)","guid":"Z1nUzfp95uWxwu60ZceV_A","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"33","text":"- Isquemia/Infarto (enfermedad coronaria, estenosis arteria del nodo)","guid":"RGJxjW2yVOkRqAF4CEKI4A","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"33","text":"- Infiltración (sarcoidosis, amiloidosis, hemocromatosis)","guid":"hbDeMLYuAlJ5RyCJ6BtR_Q","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"33","text":"- Enfermedades inflamatorias (miocarditis viral o autoinmune, fiebre reumática)","guid":"fMT_hUmCO-vuvcokQ6GXzA","children":[]},{"id":"38","parent":"33","text":"- Cirugía cardíaca previa (daño iatrogénico del nodo sinusal)","guid":"dig9dWpUBG2hawoT2Uad5Q","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"33","text":"- Enfermedades neuromusculares con afectación cardíaca (distrofia miotónica, ataxia de Friedreich)","guid":"zmjPqckPLV4ukSfuauCCDA","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"33","text":"- Otros: Tumores cardiacos, miocardiopatías, congénitas (S. de heterotaxia), postablación","guid":"upEGnIZLptzOL6wpDl-UnQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"41","parent":"28","text":"- Disfunción\\Nsinusal extrínseca","guid":"Ag8IwSDvGA6-XGa_JVFdPA","children":[{"id":"42","parent":"41","text":"- Alteraciones\\Nmetabólicas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"43","parent":"42","text":"- Hipotiroidismo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"42","text":"- Hipotermia","guid":"","